<br />
You know what always bothered me about Ghost in the Shell? They keyboard fingers. The only google example of this I can find comes from the movie, but I'm certain the android secretaries at Section 9 also do this when time is critical. While typing, the fingers and hands split open and reveal dozens of smaller metalic &quot;fingers&quot; that are then used to type even faster. But why not just skip the keyboard entirely? It's just an input device, and in a world when you can interface and manipulate a computer directly (especially in the android's case), why would you bother with a keyboard at all? Bah!
